# PRD: Add Stage - <stage-id>

## Background

This task adds a formal battle stage to the Godot fighting project using asset/data/runtime integration instead of combat-core modifications.

## Scope (In)

- Add stage background assets and optional BGM.
- Add stage data entry.
- Add stage scene if the stage needs scene-level structure.
- Wire the stage into formal runtime selection/loading.

## Scope (Out)

- New combat core rules.
- Stage hazards that require new deterministic combat systems, unless explicitly requested.
- Networking or online synchronization.

## Deliverables

1. Stage assets.
2. Stage data entry or resource.
3. Optional stage scene.
4. Runtime loading path through managers/runtime.
5. Validation notes for battle scene.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Stage can be loaded by stable stage id.
2. Formal battle loads the background and BGM correctly or gracefully falls back.
3. Fighters spawn in valid positions.
4. Runtime flow remains stable.
5. No stage logic was pushed into combat core unnecessarily.

## Guardrails

- Keep stage concerns in runtime/data/scene layers.
- Do not hardcode multiple stage paths across unrelated files.
- Prefer data registration over ad hoc scene branching.
